BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] How "Skills" solve the biggest pitfall in using AI for 
 data analysis in Claude Code & OpenAI Codex
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T090000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T100000
UID:nicar-2026-1123@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:We've all been there recently. Jazzed at experimenting with th
 e latest AI/LLM tooling to help drive our data journalism. But there remai
 ns a particularly thorny issue when using AI tools for data analysis: they
  don't do things the same way twice\, they can go rogue\, and they're awfu
 l at math. They may be great at building web apps\, but they can be very d
 angerous for doing actual data analysis. But the "skills" workflow has the
  potential to be a game-changer. They began in Claude Code and have now be
 en adopted by Codex as well. What are "skills"...? They allow you to creat
 e specific\, reproducible code chunks or even entire scripts that will the
 n get executed. The file system is dead-simple: just markdown files and yo
 ur code scripts. And from there\, skills functions largely as an automatio
 n tool - it'll run what you've told it to run\, when you tell it to\, with
  certain variables provided by you or your colleagues. And it will ensure 
 Claude or Codex gives you consistent\, reproducible results every time. Le
 arn what it's all about.\nThis session is good for people with some coding
  experience. Laptops will be provided.\n\nAI | Skill: Advanced
LOCATION:104
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1123
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Blockchain sleuthing 101
