BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Beyond ironclad: Fact-checking the data story
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T170000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T180000
UID:nicar-2026-1150@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Even with best practices\, the most meticulous data reporter i
 n the world can make mistakes. Catching these errors before publication ca
 n involve hours of tedious code review and debugging. Missing them can lea
 d to corrections\, retractions\, or worse.\nThis session will give attende
 es a hands-on demonstration of a data story fact-check. Participants will 
 learn how to spot errors in data interpretation\, how to catch and debug c
 oding errors\, and how to fix mistakes efficiently. We'll walk through an 
 example data analysis containing errors based on real mistakes made by awa
 rd-winning data journalists. (All examples will be fully anonymized!)\nSom
 e sample errors:\n- Number parsing fails due to commas as the thousands se
 parator\n- Invalid demographic analyses based on misinterpreted Census dat
 a\n- Dropped rows in joined datasets (inner joins considered harmful!)\n- 
 Unweighted aggregations of percentages and other fractions\nThis session i
 s good for those with some coding experience. Attendees will need to bring
  their own laptop (no tablets) to participate in this class.\n\nStory idea
 s | Skill: Intermediate
LOCATION:102
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1150
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
