BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Panel] Accessing data on deaths in custody
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T154500
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T164500
UID:nicar-2026-1153@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Thanks to recent FOIA lawsuits and the efforts of organization
 s like The Marshall Project\, The Data Liberation Project\, Behind Bars Da
 ta Project\, and Mapping Police Violence\, data on deaths in custody is mo
 re accessible than ever.\nThis panel will guide reporters on how to find a
 nd use this data to investigate deaths in prisons\, jails\, and police cus
 tody. Attendees will learn about what data is available\, what's missing f
 rom the data\, and how the data can reveal problematic patterns in trends 
 in the local law enforcement agencies.\n\nBeat reporting | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:White River E
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1153
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
