BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Panel] Tracking hidden money\, influence and power across borders
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T101500
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T111500
UID:nicar-2026-1219@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:From offshore accounts to complex layers of companies\, this s
 ession will show you how to follow it across borders and back again\, usin
 g public data available to any journalist. This session will show practica
 l ways to trace hidden owners\, foreign ties\, and influence networks usin
 g public records and open data. Attendees will learn proven methods to fol
 low the money\, connect global disclosures\, and turn complex data trails 
 into clear\, high-impact stories.\n\nBeat reporting\, International\, Stor
 y ideas | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:White River I
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1219
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Panel] Elections 2026: Uncovering influence operations in the U.S
 .
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T143000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T153000
UID:nicar-2026-1221@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:This panel will demonstrate how to use tools to investigate an
 d track influence operations. Journalists will learn how to piece together
  opaque spending networks and uncover crucial details about operations thr
 ough tax returns\, Foreign Agents Registration Act (FARA) filings\, digita
 l ad data\, corporate records\, lobbying disclosures and other sources.\n\
 nElections | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:White River G
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1221
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Demo] Beyond the big leagues: Data journalism in high school spor
 ts
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T090000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T100000
UID:nicar-2026-1223@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:High school sports drive huge traffic but lack the data infras
 tructure of pro leagues. This demo will explore how journalists build data
 bases and tell data-driven stories when official stats are incomplete or n
 onexistent. Panelists will share strategies for scraping and standardizing
  local sports data\, creating searchable tools for communities\, and makin
 g compelling visualizations. Attendees will learn how to find stories in o
 ft-incomplete sports data and build resources that serve coaches\, parents
 \, and fans beyond a single season.\n\nSports | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:202
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1223
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Panel] Making public data actually public: Building tools to serv
 e communities
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T143000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T153000
UID:nicar-2026-1224@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Public records are technically “public\,” but that doesn
 ’t mean they’re accessible. This panel features journalists who’ve t
 aken hard-to-use government data and transformed it into searchable databa
 ses that serve their communities. Panelists will share case studies of loo
 k up tools for stories like city council redistricting\, voter registratio
 n cancellation and more. We’ll discuss how to navigate the technical and
  editorial decisions involved in cleaning and publishing messy government 
 data\, the reality of maintaining these tools long-term\, and maintaining 
 reader/user/data privacy.\n\nTools & Tech | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:White River B
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1224
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Stadium pulse: Building sports data visualizations on d
 eadline
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T090000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T100000
UID:nicar-2026-1225@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Want to create compelling sports graphics fast? In this hands-
 on class\, you’ll build a “How’s your favorite college basketball te
 am doing?” visualization using March Madness data. We’ll use Python an
 d Jupyter notebooks to pull live data from an API\, then create charts in 
 Datawrapper. You’ll learn the workflow for going from raw data to publis
 hed graphic quickly: automating data collection\, choosing which stats tel
 l the story\, and designing for both casual fans and stats enthusiasts.\nA
 n understanding of basics in Python is helpful\, but not required\, for th
 is session. Laptops will be provided.\n\nData viz\, Sports | Skill: Interm
 ediate
LOCATION:205
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1225
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Running large language models locally\, on your compute
 r!
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T154500
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T164500
UID:nicar-2026-1226@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to run powerful language models like Llama\, Mistral
 \, and Gemma directly on your own computer. This hands-on session covers t
 he basics of local LLM deployment using LM Studio\, hardware requirements 
 (spoiler: you don't need a supercomputer)\, and practical reporting applic
 ations. We'll discuss the trade-offs between local and cloud-based models\
 , explore use cases where local models excel\, and demonstrate workflows f
 or integrating LLMs into your reporting toolkit.\nThis session is good for
  beginners and anyone who wants to learn to run LLMs locally. Laptops will
  be provided.\n\nTools & Tech | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:104
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1226
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Demo] Turn the impossible into the doable: The random sample as a
  reporting tool
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T154500
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T164500
UID:nicar-2026-1227@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:You want to know how often people get their wages garnished be
 cause of unpaid medical bills...but it would take years to comb through al
 l those court cases. Or maybe you have a long list of people deemed frauds
 ters and want to know how many of them are still operating businesses...bu
 t it would be impractical to look up each one. It's time for a random samp
 le. This session addresses how to use random sampling as a reporting tool\
 , and how to write up your findings for a lay audience. We'll review quest
 ions like: How big of a sample do you need? How can you design your random
  sample so that certain populations or geographies (like rural areas) don'
 t get ignored?\n\nData analysis | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:White River G
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1227
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Panel] Investigating the AI data center boom
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T113000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T123000
UID:nicar-2026-1228@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:This panel will discuss how to investigate the environmental a
 nd social impacts of new data centers being built in the US. Panelists wil
 l present strategies for revealing hidden costs of the data center boom\, 
 exploring how data centers strain resources and reshape rural communities\
 , particularly in drought-stricken and farming regions.\n\nStory ideas\, R
 esearch | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:White River I
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1228
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Panel] How to do data-driven work in small communities
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T154500
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T164500
UID:nicar-2026-1229@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:The Data-Driven Reporting Project was founded to support newsr
 ooms who might otherwise lack the tools\, training or capacity to do more 
 technically-focused investigative reporting. These are often smaller newsr
 ooms with fewer resources. This in-person panel discussion at NICAR will s
 how examples of how journalists\, who have received support from the Data-
 Driven Reporting Project\, are navigating complex and data-driven stories 
 on small and underserved communities. Speakers will share stories and how 
 they problem-solved connecting with the people behind the data. Good for b
 eginners.\n\nStory ideas\, Local | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:White River G
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1229
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Demo] How we cover local elections using Svelte and Datasette\, a
 nd how you can do it too
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T090000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T100000
UID:nicar-2026-1231@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Adam Marton and Jerry Zremski demonstrate how they develop the
  Local News Network's signature online voter guides -- including the one t
 hey're working on now\, which will cover every Maryland General Assembly p
 rimary this year. Using the combined power of Datasette and SvelteKit\, th
 e voter guide starts as a simple google spreadsheet before being transform
 ed into a powerful dynamic website. Jerry will talk about the editorial ef
 forts behind the voter guide and the resulting journalism and Adam will di
 scuss the nuts and bolts of development (including code that attendees can
  use to build their own site).\n\nTools & Tech | Skill: Intermediate
LOCATION:201
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1231
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Introduction to using satellite data for investigations
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T101500
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T111500
UID:nicar-2026-1232@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Satellite imagery can be a potential game-changer for investig
 ative journalists – if you know how to access\, choose\, and analyze the
  image for little to no cost. In this hands-on workshop\, a journalist wit
 h deep knowledge of satellite providers will share insider tips on how to 
 acquire medium and even high-resolution images from commercial and public 
 sources\, as well as how to filter and use these resources to give investi
 gations into topics like the scars of war or environmental disasters much 
 greater reach. This session is good for beginners. Laptops will be provide
 d.\n\nMapping\, Data analysis\, Story ideas | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:205
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1232
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
