END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] The two essential data sources for covering government 
 spending
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T143000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T153000
UID:nicar-2026-1238@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Tracking government spending has never been more convoluted. I
 n the last year\, DOGE took a “chainsaw” to federal contracts and gran
 ts\, entire departments canceled awards en masse\, and award recipients lo
 st faith in the federal government as a financial partner. In the midst of
  it all\, reporters do have public tools to dig through what some might se
 e as a trail of chaos.\nIn this session\, we will break down two specific 
 data resources any reporter needs to follow federal money: USA Spending an
 d Sam.gov. Whether reporters are interested in funds from a specific feder
 al department\, funds going to a specific county\, or even funds meant to 
 achieve a specific purpose\, this session will cover what is knowable\, ho
 w to know it\, and how to fact-check it. Panelists will also walk through 
 what is not knowable and what should always be confirmed with federal agen
 cies before going to print.\nThis session is good for all levels of experi
 ence. Laptops will be provided.\n\nBeat reporting | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:203
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1238
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] R 1: Intro to R and RStudio
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T090000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T100000
UID:nicar-2026-1239@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Jump into data analysis with R\, the powerful open-source prog
 ramming language. In this class we’ll cover R fundamentals and learn our
  way around the RStudio interface for using R.\nThis session is good for: 
 People with a basic understanding of data analysis who are ready to go bey
 ond spreadsheets. Laptops will be provided.\n\nData analysis\, Tools & Tec
 h | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:204
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1239
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] R 2: Data analysis and plotting
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T101500
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T111500
UID:nicar-2026-1240@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:We'll use the tidyverse packages dplyr and ggplot2\, learning 
 how to sort\, filter\, group\, summarize\, join\, and visualize to identif
 y trends in your data. If you want to combine SQL-like analysis and charti
 ng in a single pipeline\, this session is for you.\nThis session is good f
 or: People who have worked with data operations in SQL or Excel and would 
 like to do the same in R and have some experience working with RStudio. La
 ptops will be provided.\n\nTools & Tech | Skill: Intermediate
LOCATION:204
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1240
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] R 3: Gathering and cleaning data
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T113000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T123000
UID:nicar-2026-1241@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to import a wide variety of files in R including spr
 eadsheets\, files on the web and HTML tables\, and transform the results i
 nto usable data. This session will also focus on how to clean and structur
 e the data you've gathered in preparation for analysis using tidyverse pac
 kages.\nThis session is good for: People who have some experience using R 
 and the Tidyverse. Laptops will be provided.\n\nData analysis | Skill: Int
 ermediate
LOCATION:204
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1241
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Custom dataviz with JavaScript 101
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T143000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T153000
UID:nicar-2026-1242@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Interested in building data visualizations for the web? This s
 ession introduces the JavaScript foundations behind browser-based charts. 
 We’ll walk through core programming techniques in JavaScript like: varia
 bles\, data types\, built-in functions\, fetching external data\, and usin
 g the Document Object Model (DOM) to change a webpage. These foundations w
 ill be used to create a basic example of a visualization.\nThis is a found
 ations class for journalists who are new to JavaScript or just need a refr
 esher on some of the fundamentals. You do not need prior HTML/CSS experien
 ce\, but HTML/CSS are not taught in this session. We also won’t spend mu
 ch time building full visualizations here\; this class is designed to prep
 are you for Data Visualization 102\, where you’ll build a more complete 
 visual project.\nAttendees should bring a laptop (no tablets).\n\nData viz
  | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:102
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1242
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Custom dataviz with JavaScript 102
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T154500
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T164500
UID:nicar-2026-1243@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Interested in building data visualizations for the web? This s
 ession will continue the exploration in the 101 session of various charts 
 made with HTML\, CSS\, and JavaScript\, helping you understand how various
  components combine to create a complete visualization displayed in your b
 rowser by coding.\nThis session is good for journalists with a bit of HTML
  and CSS experience\, or participants who already attended "Custom dataviz
  with JavaScript 101". Attendees will need to bring their own laptop (no t
 ablets) to participate in this class.\n\nData viz | Skill: Intermediate
LOCATION:102
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1243
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Using Python to scrape basic websites
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T101500
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T111500
UID:nicar-2026-1245@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:This session will show you how to use the Python programming l
 anguage to scrape data from simple websites.\nThis session is good for: Pe
 ople with some experience working with data. Experience with Python and/or
  HTML is a plus but not necessary. Laptops will be provided.\n\nData analy
 sis\, Data viz\, Tools & Tech | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:104
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1245
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Using Python for data analysis
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T113000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T123000
UID:nicar-2026-1246@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Imagine rolling Excel and SQL into one tool that also allows y
 ou to track your code and share it: That's pandas in a nutshell. There's a
  lot more you can do with it\, of course\, but this will be a good start. 
 We'll learn how to slice and dice our data and extract basic stats. Specif
 ically\, we'll cover loading the data\, filtering\, sorting and grouping d
 ata.\nThis class is good for: People who are comfortable with Excel and ar
 e familiar with the basics of SQL and Python. We recommend that you attend
  a Python 101 session or have equivalent experience before coming to this 
 class.\nAttendees will need to bring their own laptop (no tablets) to part
 icipate in this class.\n\nData analysis | Skill: Intermediate
LOCATION:203
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1246
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Extracting data from PDFs using off-the-shelf tools
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T143000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T153000
UID:nicar-2026-1248@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Join this class to learn how to liberate data trapped inside P
 DF files. This class will cover basic approaches for getting text out of P
 DF documents using powerful and freely available tools. Participants will 
 be introduced to basic concepts and walked through tackling common challen
 ges encountered with tricky PDF documents.\nThis session is good for begin
 ners. Attendees will need to bring their own laptop (no tablets) to partic
 ipate in this class.\n\nTools & Tech | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:204
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1248
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] QGIS 1: Spatial analysis for beginners
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T090000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T100000
UID:nicar-2026-1249@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Learn to how to make your own maps using free\, open-source so
 ftware called QGIS. This class will teach you how to get started importing
  and displaying geographic data. Not all datasets need to be mapped\, but 
 some do! We'll go over how to find publicly available data\, prepare it fo
 r mapping\, and join together different datasets.\nThis session is good fo
 r: Beginners looking to learn the basics of visualizing geographic data. L
 aptops will be provided.\n\nData analysis | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:204
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1249
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] QGIS 2: Analyzing geographic data
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T101500
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T111500
UID:nicar-2026-1250@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Build on your existing knowledge of QGIS and learn how to expl
 ore\, manipulate and analyze geographic datasets to gain new insights.\nTh
 is session is good for: Those who attended the QGIS I workshop or already 
 know the basics of visualizing geographic data in QGIS.\n\nData analysis |
  Skill: Intermediate
LOCATION:204
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1250
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Extracting data from PDFs using command-line and other 
 advanced tools
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T143000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T153000
UID:nicar-2026-1251@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:This class seeks to help you free data stored in PDFs. Attende
 es will extract text from a computer-generated PDF using command-line tool
 s\, process image files with optical character recognition and set themsel
 ves up for working with PDFs in Python. The session will also cover how to
  assess a PDF to select the right tools to use to free its data.\nThis ses
 sion is good for: People with experience using a command-line interface an
 d who deal with frustrating PDFs. Knowledge of Python or R is a plus but n
 ot required. Laptops will be provided.\n\nTools & Tech\, Data analysis | S
 kill: Intermediate
LOCATION:205
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1251
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Finding and using undocumented APIs
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T170000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T180000
UID:nicar-2026-1252@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:This tutorial will introduce reporters to an exciting and ofte
 n overlooked data source found on every website. You will learn how to fin
 d and use hidden APIs as a reporting resource\, and hear about how this da
 ta source has been used in past reporting. We'll be working off this scrip
 ted documented: https://inspectelement.org/apis\nThis session is for repor
 ters who want to diversify their data sources. You don't need to write cod
 e: we'll teach participants to find hidden APIs in your web browser\, but 
 knowing some coding will let you to unlock detailed and rich datasets hidd
 en in plain sight. Laptops will be provided.\n\nData analysis | Skill: Beg
 inner
LOCATION:203
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1252
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Using regular expressions
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T090000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T100000
UID:nicar-2026-1253@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:By the end of this class\, this expression -- ^[A-Za-z0-9._-]+
 @[[A-Za-z0-9.-]+$ -- will make sense to you! You'll learn how to construct
  advanced searches on text data using regular expressions\, a powerful pat
 tern-matching syntax that can help you find needles in haystacks.\nThis se
 ssion is good for those with some basic experience working with data\, and
  anyone who wants to learn to use regular expressions. Laptops will be pro
 vided.\n\nData analysis | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:203
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1253
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Introduction to the command line (OSX)
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T090000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T100000
UID:nicar-2026-1254@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Too often in data journalism we forget about the basics. And i
 t doesn't get as basic as the command line. Even knowing a little will mak
 e your job easier. We will run through some simple commands\, dive into wo
 rking with spreadsheets and show you some handy tools he frequently uses a
 t work.\nThis session is good for: People who feel intimidated by the comm
 and line on their computer\, but want to explore the power of command line
  tools. Laptops will be provided.\n\nTools & Tech | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:205
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1254
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
