SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Scraping without programming (repeat)
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T170000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T180000
UID:nicar-2026-1270@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Yes\, you can scrape data without using code -- in fact\, all 
 you need is Google Sheets! We'll be using Excel-type formulas (don't worry
  if you don't know what those are\, either) to make simple scrapers that a
 utomatically pull data into Google Sheets. It’s the best way to get arou
 nd clunky websites and unhelpful PIOs!\nThis session is good for: Beginner
 s who want to start using data for their stories. Attendees will need to b
 ring their own laptop (no tablets) for the training.\n\nTools & Tech\, Dat
 a analysis | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:201
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1270
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Panel] Reporting on disappearing data about LGBTQ+ people
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T101500
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T111500
UID:nicar-2026-1271@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Reporters all over the country have scrambled to find and use 
 quality data after the federal government deleted thousands of records abo
 ut DEI\, health\, and the environment\, to name a few. But as LGBTQ+ peopl
 e are a notable target of the Trump Administration\, it's not surprising t
 hat data about LGBTQ+ people has gone dark\, been altered or is otherwise 
 now more difficult to find. Come to this session to learn about what has h
 appened to data about LGBTQ+ people\, where to find it\, and what happens 
 when you need to be your own data architect.\n\nEquity\, inclusion and acc
 essibility | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:White River I
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1271
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Fun with shapes: Scripted mapping in R or Python
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T143000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T180000
UID:nicar-2026-1272@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Let's face it\, QGIS is the Excel of geospatial analysis. Sure
 \, doing simple mapping in it and ArcGIS is a blast\, but executing comple
 x\, reproducible joins and measurements can be a real drag. Taking a more 
 scripted approach is way less of a buzzkill\, especially when you need to 
 revisit your earlier work or share with others.\nWhether you choose R or P
 ython\, follow along from mapping basics to more complex techniques that w
 ill make your next geospatial analysis a walk in the park. Cut loose\, wri
 te some replicable code and have fun with shapes!\nPreregistration is requ
 ired and seating is limited. To get the most out of this session\, you sho
 uld have a working knowledge of both GIS/mapping techniques and some exper
 ience with either Python or R. Laptops will be provided.\n\nMapping | Skil
 l: Advanced
LOCATION:205
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1272
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] Using LLMs to improve your archives
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T090000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T100000
UID:nicar-2026-1273@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Most newsroom archives contain years of institutional knowledg
 e unread by most. This session shows how to unlock them to make your repor
 ters more informed and to help onboard new journalists. Drawing on a unive
 rsity course where journalism students with little coding experience built
  "beat books" from local newspaper archives from Maryland's Eastern Shore\
 , we'll walk participants through a reproducible pipeline using open and c
 ommercial LLMs.\nLaptops will be provided.\n\nAI | Skill: Intermediate
LOCATION:205
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1273
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Hands-on] SOLD OUT - First LLM Classifier: Practical AI in the ne
 wsroom
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T090000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T123000
UID:nicar-2026-1274@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Join Ben Welsh and Andrew Briz to learn how journalists use la
 rge-language models to organize and analyze massive datasets.\nThis three-
 hour\, hands-on class will give you hands-on experience creating a machine
 -learning model that can read and categorize the text recorded in newswort
 hy datasets.\nIt will teach you how to:\n- Submit large-language model pro
 mpts with the Python programming language\n- Write structured prompts that
  can classify text into predefined categories\n- Submit dozens of prompts 
 at once as part of an automated routine\n- Evaluate results using a rigoro
 us\, scientific approach\n- Improve results by training the model with rul
 es and examples\nBy the end\, you will understand how LLM classifiers can 
 outperform traditional machine-learning methods with significantly less co
 de. And you will be ready to write a classifier on your own.\n\nAI | Skill
 : Intermediate
LOCATION:104
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1274
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Special] Journalism jobs for Internationals
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T113000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T123000
UID:nicar-2026-1275@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Things have gotten much tougher for international journalists 
 and students who want to work in the US. New policies\, hiring slowdowns a
 nd a general lack of clarity have made an already difficult process even m
 ore stressful. But you are not alone—it’s time for us to band together
 . Journalism Jobs for Internationals was created by volunteers to share re
 sources\, answer questions and build a community where international journ
 alists can support one another. In this session\, we will present what we 
 have compiled\, answer your questions and listen to your feedback. Help us
  better help you!\n\nInternational | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:White River E
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1275
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Master Class] Managing investigators: Leading those born to chall
 enge authority
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T090000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T111500
UID:nicar-2026-1276@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Being a news manager is already tough\, but what if you superv
 ise investigative journalists? They come with an extra layer of challenges
  because their very job (and likely their personality) makes them hyper-al
 ert to authority figures. This course is designed to give you some tools a
 nd tactics to lead individuals and entire teams of investigators more effe
 ctively. Learn from three investigative managers from different media at d
 ifferent stages of their leadership careers. How did they launch into thei
 r roles\, and what experience have they gained along the way? This course 
 is for current investigative managers and anyone aspiring to step into suc
 h a position in the future.\nNEW AT NICAR26: We’ll tailor portions of th
 is course for people who may be navigating AI and also offer details on IR
 E’s new Managers of Color cohort. We’re also squeezing it into two hou
 rs of learning\, then an hour-long management networking/meetup event. Oh
 … and it’s free to attend (typically\, an additional fee is required)!
 \nTopics will include: managing compassionately\, hiring challenges\, tran
 sitioning to management\, forging partnerships\, building relationships\, 
 handling resource cuts\, organization/structure\, tough decisions/conversa
 tions\, in-house training/growth\, delivering feedback\, creating inclusiv
 e opportunities\, and juggling responsibilities/projects/work.\n\nManageme
 nt | Skill: Intermediate
LOCATION:209
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1276
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Special] Mentor program breakfast (invitation-only event)
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T074500
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T084500
UID:nicar-2026-1277@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:If you signed up for the conference mentor program\, come meet
  your match at this invitation-only breakfast.\n\nEvent | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:Griffin Hall
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1277
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
