BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Demo] Catching the quiet changes: Automating website monitoring f
 or investigative journalism with Visualping
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T090000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T100000
UID:nicar-2026-1348@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:In this session\, you'll learn how to use Visualping\, an AI w
 ebsite change detection tool\, to automatically monitor and get instant al
 erts for important changes to any websites you need to track for your beat
 \, whether it's local court dockets\, government agency websites\, a polit
 ician's social media pages\, or something else. We'll walk through setting
  up a Visualping alert\, using different features and settings\, and tips 
 for using Visualping's AI criteria and summary features.\nAttendees are we
 lcome to sign up for a free Visualping account at visualping.io to follow 
 along.\n\nTools & Tech | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:White River I
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1348
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Demo] Finding a needle in a haystack: How to manage document-heav
 y investigations
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T113000
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T123000
UID:nicar-2026-1349@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Searching for relevant evidence for a story through a never-en
 ding pile of documents\, legal forms\, contracts\, emails\, videos\, or ce
 ll phone data can be taxing and time-consuming\, even for the best investi
 gative teams out there.\nThe team at Everlaw will demonstrate their tools 
 to help with automatic transcription of audio and video (think bodycam foo
 tage\, depositions\, interview recordings)\, making documents text-searcha
 ble through optical character recognition\, file management tools (like se
 arch\, labeling\, AI summaries)\, analysis tools (like data viz and topic 
 clustering)\, and story-building tools (drafting\, citations\, and AI writ
 ing assistance). They'll show how newsrooms like the San Francisco Chronic
 le\, ProPublica and Fast Company uncover key information using their tool.
 \nYou'll also learn about Everlaw’s free offering for journalists\, whic
 h includes unlimited users\, training and support at no extra cost.\n\nToo
 ls & Tech | Skill: Beginner
LOCATION:White River G
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1349
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Panel] How to turn local data into far more useful tools for your
  newsroom — and your audiences
DTSTART;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T154500
DTEND;TZID=EST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260305T164500
UID:nicar-2026-1350@ire.org
DESCRIPTION:Local data like election results\, campaign finance\, and scho
 ol budgets can become core infrastructure for your newsroom\, helping repo
 rters add context and depth to their stories that no one else will have. A
 nd while they support your editorial department\, those same data tools ca
 n also help your newsroom launch useful and engaging news products. Learn 
 about two such projects underway in Lancaster County\, Pa. and at The Texa
 s Tribune and see how they are designing and building core data infrastruc
 ture to support stronger local government coverage.\n\nPublic records | Sk
 ill: Beginner
LOCATION:White River G
URL:https://schedules.ire.org/nicar-2026#session-1350
X-SOURCE:NICAR 2026
END:VEVENT
